<div class="main-content wide-content">

  <div class="panel-content">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="accordion">
          <h3 class="">What is website-targeted lead generation?</h3>
          <div class="pane" style="display: block;">
            <p>Simply put, it is the practice of downloading a website and collecting all the contact info contained within, which makes prospecting 100x easier.</p>
          </div>
          <h3>How does it work?</h3>
          <div class="pane" style="display: block;">
            <p>We've put together a distributed grid computing system that combines thousands of computers to provide computing power and bandwidth for ContactRocket users.  When a user submits a job, that job is processed by ContactRocket' back-end and then URLs to scan are distributed (along with the user's special rocket) to the thousands of computers in the grid.  Once each computer scans and processes the content at its designated set of URLs, the results are sent back to ContactRocket and compiled for the user.</p>
          </div>

          <h3>What is a Match?</h3>
          <div class="pane" style="display: block;">
            <p>You specify a set of urls and ContactRocket runs a scan in our distributed cloud and gives you contacts matched by type. Cloud computers take advantage of our data-match algorithms.  More advanced engines can control the scan and/or control the analysis that is done on the page content accessed during the scan.</p>
          </div>

          <h3>How fast is this thing?</h3>
          <div class="pane" style="display: block;">
<p>The scan performance of ContactRocket primarily depends on 2 factors.  The first is which domain(s) you're scanning and the second is how many domains you're scanning simultaneously.  ContactRocket will only scan a domain as fast as the system believes it can be scanned without overloading the domain.  However, it can scan several domains in parallel without any bottleneck.  What this means is that scan speed bottlenecks are rarely on the side of ContactRocket.  You will always be scanning as quickly as possible for the website(s) you're targeting. </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div><!-- Panel Content -->

